            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Has a decision been made about this? The current configuration installs Neovim per-machine (all users) but only adds it to the Path per-user (single user). So, changing the setting back to `System='yes'` seems like the right decision to me.\r\n\r\nThe previous problem regarding privileges when upgrading versions (#22933) come from the  fact that users were upgrading across installations context, [which isn't supported or recommended](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/15492415/windows-installer-changing-installation-policy-during-upgrade-causing-duplicat)",
